<TITLE> Poet, journalist Abu Kaiser's death anniversary observed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tangail, May 1 (bdnews24.com)The fourth death anniversary of poet and journalist Abu Kaiser was observed in a low-key manner Friday. Reclusive, publicity-shy, Kaiser was one of the leading poets of 1960s. He was born in Ziagonj, Murshidabad of West Bengal and grew up in Tangail. He died of cardiac diseases and other complications in 2005 at National Institute of Chest Diseases and Hospital in Mohakhali in Dhaka. Kaiser was laid to rest at his village Nandir Betka in Tangail according to his wishes. He worked with the Daily Jugantar as an assistant editor until his last days. His family arranged a Quarankhani and Milad Mahfil at a local mosque. The senior journalist worked in the daily Ittefaq, Bichitra, Saptahik Biplob, Dainik Bangla, Gonokantha, Bhorer Kagoj and other leading dailies and periodicals. Kaiser has 50 books published on poems, short stories, biographies, novels and children' literature. His books have been translated in English, Hindi, German, French and Russian languages. He won Agrani Bank Children's Literature Award in 1986 and 1989, Freedom Fighter Writers' Award, M Nurul Quader Foundation Children Literature awards, among others. bdn
